    "body": "The `-assumevalid` option skips script verification for a specified block and all its ancestors during Initial Block Download.\r\nMany first-time users are surprised when this suddenly slows their node to a halt.\r\nThis commit adds a log message to clearly indicate when this optimization ends and full validation begins.\r\n\r\nThe message is logged exactly once, when script validation is enabled **and** the previous block's hash matches the one set by [`-assumevalid`](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/12fb00fd4228ad5158fd4893e7804d5667ea700b/src/init.cpp#L469).\r\n\r\nThe log message is styled to be consistent with the existing [\"Assuming ancestors of block %s have valid signatures\"](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/0cdddeb2240d1f33c8b2dd28bb0c9d84d9420e3d/src/node/chainstate.cpp#L148) message.\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n<summary>Testing instructions</summary>\r\n\r\nFor debugging I've added:\r\n```C++\r\nstd::cout << \"fScriptChecks = \" << fScriptChecks << \", script_check_started = \" << script_check_started << std::endl;\r\n```\r\nwhich goes through these stages:\r\n* `fScriptChecks = 0, script_check_started = 0`\r\n* `fScriptChecks = 1, script_check_started = 0`\r\n* `Started signature validation at block ...`\r\n* `fScriptChecks = 1, script_check_started = 1`\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncmake -B build && cmake --build build && mkdir -p demo\r\nbuild/bin/bitcoind -datadir=demo -stopatheight=1010 -assumevalid=00000000c937983704a73af28acdec37b049d214adbda81d7e2a3dd146f6ed09 | egrep 'ancestors of block|validation at block'\r\n```\r\nwhich should show these two lines:\r\n* > Assuming ancestors of block [00000000c937983704a73af28acdec37b049d214adbda81d7e2a3dd146f6ed09](https://mempool.space/block/00000000c937983704a73af28acdec37b049d214adbda81d7e2a3dd146f6ed09) have valid signatures.\r\n* > Started signature validation at block [00000000a2887344f8db859e372e7e4bc26b23b9de340f725afbf2edb265b4c6](https://mempool.space/block/00000000a2887344f8db859e372e7e4bc26b23b9de340f725afbf2edb265b4c6).\r\n\r\nfollowed by adding `-minimumchainwork=0`\r\n```bash\r\nbuild/bin/bitcoind -datadir=demo -stopatheight=1010 -assumevalid=00000000c937983704a73af28acdec37b049d214adbda81d7e2a3dd146f6ed09 -reindex-chainstate -minimumchainwork=0\r\n```\r\n(having the same output)\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nbuild/bin/bitcoind -datadir=demo -stopatheight=1010 -reindex-chainstate -assumevalid=0 | egrep 'Script verification|validation at block'\r\n```\r\n* > Script verification uses 15 additional threads\r\n\r\nor full IBD/reindex without explicit `-assumevalid`:\r\n```bash\r\nbuild/bin/bitcoind -datadir=demo -stopatheight=900000 -reindex-chainstate | grep -C2 '886157'\r\n```\r\n* > UpdateTip: new best=00000000000000000001b658dd1120e82e66d2790811f89ede9742ada3ed6d77 height=886157 version=0x22024000 log2_work=95.475345 tx=1161875261 date='2025-03-03T15:52:21Z' progress=0.956022 cache=4682.3MiB(34814627txo)\r\n* > Started signature validation at block 000000000000000000022614dc170eadb7b544824cbcdb0732bdeca42839aa37.\r\n* > UpdateTip: new best=000000000000000000022614dc170eadb7b544824cbcdb0732bdeca42839aa37 height=886158 version=0x24c3a000 log2_work=95.475357 tx=1161878233 date='2025-03-03T15:56:42Z' progress=0.956023 cache=4682.3MiB(34814461txo)\r\n\r\n</details>\r\n",
